olet di Albenga'' (natural genetic mutation), open-pollinated purple variety.", "traits": "Deep purple spears (color fades to green when cooked), attractive appearance, purple tips and bracts.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate to good. Male and female plants (60% male), fewer but larger spears. Less productive than all-male green varieties but compensates with superior flavor.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Sweet Purple", "slug": "sweet-purple", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Italian heritage, cold-hardy purple variety.", "traits": "Bold purple color throughout, distinctive appearance.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good. Male and female plants mix.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available - True Leaf Market (crowns), international suppliers, select Australian nurseries."}, {"name": "Erasmus F1", "slug": "erasmus-f1", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 15, "origin": "UK, 2012. First all-male purple hybrid asparagus, breakthrough variety.", "traits": "Deep purple spears with tight tips, mild color, brilliant purple when raw.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Very high - revolutionary for purple varieties. All-male hybrid, yields 2-3x other purple varieties, on par with green varieties.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Limited in Australia - Gurney''s (US), European suppliers, specialty import may be required."}, {"name": "Precoce D''Argenteuil (Early Argenteuil) 🏆", "slug": "precoce-d-argenteuil-early-argenteuil", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 16, "origin": "France, 1885. Vilmorin-Andrieux selection from ''Giant Dutch Purple''. Argenteuil district near Paris, famous asparagus region since 1800s.", "traits": "Thick rose-purple spears when unblanched, attractive rosy pink tips, pale green when blanched (White Gold), 60-90cm tall at maturity.", "flesh_f